# Security Policy

## Supported Versions

Security updates are provided for the latest released version of [% .ProjectName %].
If you maintain older versions, document any additional supported branches here.

| Version | Supported |
| ------- | --------- |
| Latest  | Yes       |
| Older   | No        |

## Reporting a Vulnerability

Please report suspected vulnerabilities privately. Do not open a public issue for
security-sensitive reports.

Send your report to the maintainer security contact for this project. If no
private contact is listed, ask the maintainers for a private reporting channel at
[% .RepoURL %]/issues before sharing vulnerability details.

Include:

- Affected version or commit
- Steps to reproduce or proof of concept
- Impact and any known mitigations
- Your preferred contact for follow-up

## Response Expectations

Maintainers will acknowledge valid reports as soon as practical, investigate the
impact, and coordinate with the reporter on remediation. Updates may include
confirmation, mitigation guidance, expected fix timing, or a decision that the
report is not a vulnerability.

## Public Disclosure

Public disclosure should be coordinated with maintainers and normally happens
after a fix or mitigation is available. Release notes or advisories should credit
reporters when requested and include enough detail for users to assess and update
without exposing unnecessary exploit guidance.
